<paragraph blockId="47.[151,1437,726,931]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
Two species comprise the 
<taxonomicName box="[447,542,726,750]" class="Insecta" family="Hydraenidae" genus="Hydraena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="136" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="clystera">
<emphasis box="[447,542,726,750]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Clystera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Complex: 
<taxonomicName box="[675,799,726,751]" class="Insecta" family="Hydraenidae" genus="Hydraena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="clystera">
<emphasis box="[675,799,726,751]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">H. clystera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<emphasis box="[861,1011,726,751]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">H. d-concava</emphasis>
. These are medium sized species (ca. 
<quantity box="[151,318,762,786]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.295" metricValueMax="1.31" metricValueMin="1.28" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" unit="mm" value="1.295" valueMax="1.31" valueMin="1.28">1.28–1.31 mm</quantity>
), which have a moderately sparsely punctate and shining dorsum, a subcordiform pronotum (with or without a dark fascia), and a diffuse, lightly colored elytral macula (
<figureCitation box="[915,1054,798,822]" captionStart-0="FIGURE 91" captionStart-1="FIGURE 92" captionStartId-0="135.[151,250,1650,1673]" captionStartId-1="136.[151,250,1630,1653]" captionTargetBox-0="[265,1321,193,1626]" captionTargetBox-1="[226,1357,193,1605]" captionTargetId-0="figure@135.[265,1322,193,1629]" captionTargetId-1="figure@136.[226,1360,193,1609]" captionTargetPageId-0="135" captionTargetPageId-1="136" captionText-0="FIGURE 91. Hydraena clystera, holotype, dorsal and lateral habitus, and venter." captionText-1="FIGURE 92. Hydraena d-concava, holotype, dorsal and lateral habitus, and venter." httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/1050160/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/1050162/files/figure.png" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
Figs. 
<number box="[979,1054,798,822]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" value="91.5" valueMax="92.0" valueMin="91.0">91–92</number>
</figureCitation>
). The metaventrite has a deep, triangular impression. The aedeagus in this complex is very unusual: there is no distal piece, the gonopore being located at the sharply pointed end of the main piece (
<figureCitation box="[755,895,870,894]" captionStart="FIGURES 93 – 95" captionStartId="137.[151,264,1650,1673]" captionText="FIGURES 93 – 95. Aedeagi of holotypes." pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
Figs. 
<number box="[820,895,870,894]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" value="94.5" valueMax="95.0" valueMin="94.0">94–95</number>
</figureCitation>
). The currently known species are from 
<collectingCountry box="[1354,1437,870,894]" name="Bolivia" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
(
<taxonomicName box="[160,283,907,931]" class="Insecta" family="Hydraenidae" genus="Hydraena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="clystera">
<emphasis box="[160,283,907,931]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">H. clystera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and 
<taxonomicName box="[354,406,907,930]" class="Insecta" family="Hydraenidae" genus="Hydraena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="167" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peru">
<collectingCountry box="[354,406,907,930]" name="Peru" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Peru</collectingCountry>
</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis box="[421,571,907,931]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">H. d-concava</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
